{{Infobox book | name = The Clock Without A Face | title_orig = | translator = | image = CWAF-book-picture.jpg | caption = The book is shaped like a house | author = Eli Horowitz, Mac Barnett | illustrator = Scott Teplin | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = | genre = [[Mystery fiction|Mystery]], [[Puzzle book]] | publisher = [[McSweeney's]] | pub_date = May 2010 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print ([[Board book]]) | pages = 30 | isbn = 978-1-934781-71-5 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} {{Portal |Children's literature}}
'''''The Clock Without a Face''''' is [[puzzle book]] by Eli Horowitz and [[Mac Barnett]] with illustrations by Scott Teplin. It was published in 2010 by [[McSweeney's]]. The plot of the book revolves around the theft of 12 jeweled numbers from the face of "the Emerald Khroniker," a cursed clock, and with clues to the thief's identity and the whereabouts of the numbers are included throughout the text and in accompanying pictures. The identity of the thieves is revealed on the last page, but the location of the loot is not. The authors hid 12 actual emerald-studded numbers (crafted by [[Anna Sheffield]]) in locations around the United States, and readers are encouraged to search for them using the clues in the book.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weeklydig.com/arts-entertainment/words/201005/clock-without-face|title=THE CLOCK WITHOUT A FACE |last=Day|first=David|publisher=Weekly Dig|accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://chicago.timeout.com/articles/books/85263/the-clock-without-a-face-scott-teplin-mac-barnett-eli-horowitz-book-review|title=The Clock Without a Face - Scott Teplin, Mac Barnett, Eli Horowitz - Book Review - Time Out Chicago|last=Messinger|first=Jonathan|work=Time Out Chicago|accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.sfgate.com/2010-04-30/entertainment/20876930_1_book-clock-authors|title=Clues in book will lead to buried treasure|last=Vaziri|first=Aidin|date=April 30, 2010|work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|publisher=San Francisco Chronicle|accessdate=2 June 2010}}</ref><ref name="WeSat">{{cite web|title= Read This Book And Join The Treasure Hunt|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=127790285|work=NPR|accessdate=12 June 2010}}</ref>
